Sec. 74.002. DEFINITIONS. In this subchapter:
(1) "Cotton" includes the cotton plant, cotton in the boll,
cotton stalk, and all cotton products, including seed cotton,
cottonseed, and cotton hulls, but not including cotton oil or cotton
meal.
(2) "Cotton pest" includes the boll weevil and the pink
bollworm.
(3) "Host plant" means a plant susceptible to infestation
by the boll weevil, pink bollworm, or any other cotton pest.
(4) "Boll weevil" means the insect Anthonomus grandis
Boheman, in any stage of development, including the egg, larval,
pupal, and adult stages.
(5) "Okra" includes okra stalks.
(6) "Pest management zone" means a geographical zone
established by the department under this chapter for purposes of
cotton pest control and prevention.
(7) "Pink bollworm" means the insect Pectinophora
gossypiella, Saunders, in any stage of development, including the
egg, larval, pupal, and adult stages.
Amended by Acts 1987, 70th Leg., ch. 691, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1987;
Acts 1995, 74th Leg., ch. 957, Sec. 2, eff. June 16, 1995.

